profile_positions.description:
Backend .NET Framework / C# Software Engineer at Baker Hughes Company
in Celle Technology Center (CTC, Germany).

Summary:
Working with the two major business enterprise systems to communicate between the surface devices located on drilling rigs (e.g. SOLUS Data Acquisition Unit, ABPA) and underground tools: transformers, stabilizers, commanders, sensors, etc. used in wellbores to achieve controllable, efficient steered drilling and fast telemetry. Collaboration with drilling engineers, SMEs, developers, UX/UI designers, and testers.

Responsibilities:
– Implementing new business functionalities/mechanics/services (mostly backend, sometimes UI);
– Maintaining and supporting existing solutions;
– Designing and improving software architecture (SOLID, design patterns, MVVM);
– Refactoring, optimization, MSDN standards;
– Unit/integration tests, TDD, code coverage;
– Writing technical documentation (code and UML);
– Member of "Architecture Working Group" (AWG);
– Mentorship of junior software developers

Achievements:
– Migration to Git from TFVC for Baker Hughes CTC (Celle Technology Center);
   tech supervision and international training/workshops (Germany, India, US,
   Scotland, The Netherlands) dedicated to using Git, GitFlow, clean branching
   strategies, and Pull Requests during the development life-cycle

Technologies:
– .NET Framework (C# 6.0, WPF, XAML), LINQ, SQL (MS SQL Server 2017), Entity Framework 6,
   unit-testing (MS Test 2), mocking frameworks (Moq, Rhino), DI (Castle Core), Microsoft TFS,
   version control systems (TFVC, Git), communication protocols (OPC/UA)

Methodologies/frameworks:
– Agile SCRUM, Kanban

Additional skills:
– Working in an international environment (English-based);
– Leading feature-oriented subteams and engineering workgroups;
– Public speeches and technical workshops

Agnostic Fullstack Software Developer (Python, Java SE, .NET / C#).

Summary:
Developing client-oriented, small and medium, web-based applications for the
Hungarian/Polish software house company (startup). Frequent contact with the client.

Responsibilities:
– Developing new functionalities, migrating systems;
– Co-planning database and application architectures;
– Writing technical documentation, UML, and charts;
– Writing unit tests (TDD approach in general);
– UX design after consultation with the client

Technologies:
– Backend: Python, Java SE, C#, Unity 3D,
algorithms and data structures, optimization (Big-O), unit testing (TDD, BDD);
– Databases: SQL, SQLite, MySQL, Microsoft SQL Server, LINQ to SQL, Entity Framework;
– Frontend: HTML5, CSS3, Bootstrap, FlexBox, JavaScript, jQuery, Flask, Jinja2, Spark, Thymeleaf, ASP.NET MVC, Razor, creating (or migrating and enhancing to from console API) web-based applications;
– DVCS: working with Git in 4-5 people teams with the Product Owner;
– Other: LINQ, RegEx

Soft skills:
– cooperation, communication, teamwork, business mindset, public presentations;
– Agile/SCRUM framework, basics of Continuous Integration (docker + Jenkins);
– Role of Team Leader (5 people);
– Role of SCRUM Master (4 teams)

Additional skills:
– Working in the semi-international environment
(Poland, Hungary);
– Helping new teams to organize their SCRUM workflow
